If we want to use a different separator, for example an underscore, we could do something like the following:

```
    DecimalFormatSymbols sym = new DecimalFormatSymbols() {
      private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;
      @Override
      public char getGroupingSeparator() {
        return '_';
      }
    };
    
    DecimalFormat newFormat = new DecimalFormat(((DecimalFormat) DecimalFormat.getInstance()).toPattern(), sym);
    System.out.println(newFormat.format(123456789L));
```

Note that DecimalFormat is not thread safe.
